            <creation>This story, with the short title "Blind and Paralyzed Man Healed," is very old: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1404</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>A man named Wafelqalonie had been blind and paralyzed since birth. When he prayed for Mary to heal him, the Holy Virgin appeared, blessed him, and directed his prayer to God. Wafelqalonie then responded with a prayer for Christ to spare him on the day of Judgment. Elsewhere, a judge called to Mary to save him when his boat was about to sink in the sea. Mary prayed to Christ, and the judge was saved, along with all his servants and possessions.</p>
            </abstract>
